headline: Amazon’s Prime Video Acquires Melania Trump Film
summary: Amazon.com  Prime Video streaming service has licensed what it said was a documentary about former and future first lady  Melania Trump.  The film is being done with her cooperation, and she will have an executive producer credit on the movie, Amazon said Sunday.  Filming of the “behind-the-scenes” look at her life began in December, a month after President-elect  Donald Trump’s  election victory.

headline: 1 Wall Street Analyst Thinks Meta Platforms Stock Is Going to $750. Is It a Buy?
summary: Shares of Meta Platforms (NASDAQ: META) fell to a cheap valuation in 2022 and have soared almost 400% over the last two years.  JMP Securities analyst Andrew Boone recently raised the firm's price target to $750, implying upside of 25% over the current $599 share price, and maintained an outperform (buy) rating on the stock.  The analyst sees several reasons to be bullish on the social media leader's growth prospects.
